Philippine Stocks: Metro Pacific Investments, PNOC Exploration

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m   a n d   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-05-10T04:20:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/philippine-stocks-metro-pacific-philippine-long-distance.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 45.98 points, or
1.1 percent, to 4,303.13, the steepest advance since April 25.  Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  , a water utility
and toll-road company, gained 2.3 percent to 3.60 pesos, the
first increase since April 29. The company’s first-quarter net
income rose to 820 million pesos ($19 million) from 650 million
pesos a year earlier, driven by earnings from its water and
electricity businesses, it said in a statement yesterday.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , the
country’s most valuable company, jumped 3.1 percent to 2,480
pesos, the steepest increase since March 30. PLDT’s first-
quarter profit was “better than expected,” Chairman Manuel
Pangilinan told reporters in Manila yesterday. The results are
scheduled to be released today.  PNOC Exploration Corp. (PECB)  , the state-owned oil and
gas company, advanced 1.5 percent to 66 pesos. The company said
ATR Kim Eng Financial Corp., Citigroup Inc., Deutsche Bank AG
and UBS AG were shortlisted to bid for a deal to be the
company’s financial adviser for a planned share sale, it said in
a disclosure to the stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
